Company Description                    




                        CAVALI, since its inception in 1987, assumed a strategic role for the orderly growth of the Peruvian stock market. The company's sole object, record keeping, custody and settlement of securities, emission of instruments and derivative instruments authorized by CONASEV. The organization and operation of CAVALI is subject to the Securities Market Act and its regulations issued by the National Supervisory Commission of Companies and Securities-CONASEV. The company also is listed in the Lima Stock Exchange since 2007.                    


